# ECE PORTFOLIO — PROJECT CONSTITUTION
# This file is the supreme law of this codebase.
# All AI agents must read this entire file before generating any code.
# Violations of these laws will be caught in code review and rejected.

===============================================================================
LAW 1: THE PHYSICS ENGINE LAW
===============================================================================
CSS transitions are BANNED for interactive elements.
The following patterns will cause your output to be REJECTED:

  BANNED: transition: all 0.3s ease;
  BANNED: transition: opacity 0.2s ease-in-out;
  BANNED: animation: fadeIn 0.5s linear;
  BANNED: @keyframes used on user-interactive elements

REQUIRED: All interactive motion uses Framer Motion with explicit spring physics.
Template (copy and customize values — never use defaults blindly):

  <motion.div
    whileHover={{ scale: 1.02, y: -2 }}
    whileTap={{ scale: 0.98 }}
    transition={{ type: "spring", stiffness: 400, damping: 30, mass: 1 }}
  />

Spring presets (defined in DESIGN_SYSTEM.md):
  - Default:  { stiffness: 400, damping: 30, mass: 1 }
  - Snappy:   { stiffness: 600, damping: 40, mass: 0.8 }
  - Heavy:    { stiffness: 200, damping: 25, mass: 1.5 }

The UI must feel like it has physical mass. Every interaction must feel like
touching real hardware. If it doesn't feel physical, it is wrong.

===============================================================================
LAW 2: THE TYPESCRIPT LAW
===============================================================================
TypeScript strict mode is ACTIVE. The build will FAIL on violations.

  BANNED: any — do not use this type under any circumstance
  BANNED: @ts-ignore — do not suppress type errors
  BANNED: @ts-expect-error — do not suppress type errors
  BANNED: as unknown as X — do not use double casting to escape the type system
  BANNED: Implicit return types on exported functions

REQUIRED patterns:
  - All API response shapes must have explicit interfaces in src/core/types/
  - All React components typed as: const ComponentName: React.FC<Props> = ...
  - All async functions typed with explicit return: async function foo(): Promise<Bar>
  - All hardware model data typed with generics — no raw object shapes

If you need to use a third-party library that has poor types, create a
declaration file in src/core/types/declarations.d.ts and document why.

===============================================================================
LAW 3: THE CONTEXT HANDOVER LAW
===============================================================================
Before ending any session, you MUST output a JSON payload and write it
to docs/LATEST_STATE.json. The format is:

{
  "last_updated": "<ISO 8601 datetime>",
  "last_agent": "<your agent name>",
  "completed_today": ["<exact description of what you finished>"],
  "currently_broken": ["<exact description of what is broken and why>"],
  "open_blockers": ["<anything blocking the next agent>"],
  "next_agent_directive": {
    "agent": "<which agent goes next>",
    "action": "<exact instruction for what they must do first>"
  }
}

Failure to update LATEST_STATE.json means the next agent starts blind.
This is the most operationally critical law in the project.

===============================================================================
LAW 4: THE ISOLATION LAW
===============================================================================
Domain boundaries are ABSOLUTE. Importing across domain lines is BANNED.

  BANNED: Importing from src/glsl inside src/components
  BANNED: Importing from src/components inside src/glsl
  BANNED: Importing CSS/Tailwind classes inside src/core
  BANNED: Using Three.js/R3F state directly inside React DOM components
  BANNED: Using React DOM APIs (useRef to DOM elements) inside src/glsl scenes

REQUIRED: Use Zustand as the ONLY bridge between the WebGL canvas and the DOM.
  - The Zustand store lives in: src/core/store/
  - src/glsl reads from and writes to the Zustand store
  - src/components reads from and writes to the Zustand store
  - src/glsl and src/components never communicate directly

The isolation law exists to prevent GPU memory leaks. Three.js creates
WebGL contexts that do not garbage-collect with React's DOM lifecycle.
Mixing them causes the browser to crash on mobile devices.

===============================================================================
LAW 5: THE PERFORMANCE LAW
===============================================================================
Target: 100/100 Lighthouse score on mobile. Non-negotiable.

  BANNED: Client Components for content that can be Server Components
  BANNED: Importing entire icon libraries (import * from 'lucide-react')
  BANNED: Synchronous data fetching that blocks the render
  BANNED: Images without next/image optimization
  BANNED: Fonts loaded from external CDN (use next/font only)

REQUIRED:
  - All static content pages use React Server Components (no 'use client')
  - 'use client' is only permitted for: animation, WebGL, user interaction
  - All images use Next.js <Image> component with explicit width/height
  - All fonts loaded via next/font/google with display: 'swap'
  - Dynamic imports with loading states for all heavy components (Three.js)

===============================================================================
LAW 6: THE COMMIT LAW
===============================================================================
Every commit must follow Conventional Commits format exactly:

  feat(scope): description       ← New feature
  fix(scope): description        ← Bug fix
  docs(scope): description       ← Documentation only
  style(scope): description      ← CSS/visual only, no logic change
  refactor(scope): description   ← Code restructure, no behavior change
  perf(scope): description       ← Performance improvement
  chore(scope): description      ← Build, config, dependency changes

Valid scopes: webgl, ui, core, animation, mdx, api, config, docs, scripts

Examples:
  feat(webgl): add liquid metal shader with mouse physics
  fix(animation): correct spring damping on hero button entrance
  perf(core): memoize GitHub GraphQL query result
  chore(config): add Zustand to dependency list

One commit = one atomic change. Do not bundle unrelated work.
